{{Infobox settlement |official_name = Centennial Park, Arizona |settlement_type = [[Census-designated place|CDP]] |image_skyline = |imagesize = |image_caption = |image_seal = <!-- Maps --> |pushpin_map = USA Arizona#USA |pushpin_label_position = <!-- the position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none --> |pushpin_map_caption = Location within the state of Arizona |pushpin_mapsize = |image_map = |map_caption = Location within Mohave County |subdivision_type = [[Countries of the World|Country]] |subdivision_type1 = [[U.S. state|State]] |subdivision_type2 = [[List of counties in Arizona|County]] |subdivision_name = [[United States]] |subdivision_name1 = [[Arizona]] |subdivision_name2 = [[Mohave County, Arizona|Mohave]] |government_type = |leader_title = |leader_name = |established_date = |area_magnitude = |area_total_km2 = 5.62 |area_total_sq_mi = 2.17 |area_land_km2 = 5.62 |area_land_sq_mi = 2.17 |area_water_km2 = 0.00 |area_water_sq_mi = 0.00 |elevation_ft = 4915 |elevation_m = 1498 |elevation_footnotes = <ref name=GNIS>{{Cite GNIS|2582750|Feature Detail Report for: Centennial Park Census Designated Place}}</ref> |population_as_of = [[2010 United States Census|2010]] |population_footnotes = |population_total = 5015 |population_metro = |population_density_km2 = NaN |population_density_sq_mi = NaN |timezone = [[Mountain Standard Time Zone|MST]] |utc_offset = -7 |coordinates = {{coord|36|57|14|N|112|58|53|W|region:US_type:city|display=inline,title}} |timezone_DST = |utc_offset_DST = |postal_code_type = |postal_code = |area_code = 928 |blank_name = [[Federal Information Processing Standard|FIPS code]] |blank_info = 04-11500 |blank1_name = [[Geographic Names Information System|GNIS]] feature ID |blank1_info = 2582750 |footnotes = |website = |pop_est_as_of = 2016 |pop_est_footnotes = <ref name="USCensusEst2016">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2016.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|accessdate=June 9, 2017}}</ref> |population_est = N/A |unit_pref = Imperial |area_footnotes = <ref name="CenPopGazetteer2016">{{cite web|title=2016 U.S. Gazetteer Files|url=https://www2.census.gov/geo/docs/maps-data/data/gazetteer/2016_Gazetteer/2016_gaz_place_04.txt|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=Jul 18, 2017}}</ref> }}
'''Centennial Park ''' is a [[census-designated place]] (CDP) in [[Mohave County, Arizona|Mohave County]], [[Arizona]], [[United States]]. The population was 1264 at the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]]. It is the central location for the [[Centennial Park group]], a [[Mormon fundamentalism|fundamentalist Mormon]] group.
==Geography== Crozier is located at {{coord|36|57|14|N|112|58|53|W|type:city}} (36.953806, -112.981325). According to the [[United States Geological Survey]], the CDP has a total area of {{convert|2.17|sqmi|km2}}, all of it land.<ref name=GNIS />
==Demographics== {{US Census population |footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref name="DecennialCensus">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/prod/www/decennial.html|title=Census of Population and Housing|publisher=Census.gov|accessdate=June 4, 2016}}</ref> }} As of the 2010 census, there were 1264 people residing in the CDP: 569 male and 695 female. 781 were 19 years old or younger, 242 were ages 20–34, 153 were between the ages of 35 and 49, 67 were between 50 and 64, and the remaining 21 were aged 65 and above. The median age was 15.0 years.
The racial makeup of the CDP was 94.6% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], 0.2% [[Race (United States Census)|Black or African American]], 0.2% [[Race (United States Census)|Asian]], 0.1% [[Race (United States Census)|Native Hawaiian]], 2.0% [[Race (United States Census)|Other]], and 2.9% [[Race (United States Census)|two or more races]]. 5.1% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race.
There were 207 households in the CDP, 187 family households (90.3%) and 20 non-family households (9.7%), with an average household size of 6.11. Of the family households, 127 were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, with 20 single father and 40 single mother households, while the non-family households included 17 adults living alone: 5 male and 12 female.
The CDP contained 225 housing units, of which 207 were occupied and 18 were vacant.<ref name=GR2>{{cite web|url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US0411500 | title=American FactFinder: Centennial Park CDP, Arizona |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |accessdate=November 10, 2016 |deadurl=no}}</ref>
