anese village braces for Syrian assault|url=http://www.csmonitor.com/World/Middle-East/2014/0423/Encircled-and-alone-Lebanese-village-braces-for-Syrian-assault|accessdate=9 December 2015|work=The Christian Science Monitor|date=23 April 2014}}</ref>
On 1 May 2014, Tfail was the [[List of Syrian Civil War barrel bomb attacks#May|target]] of Syrian barrel bomb attacks. During the [[Qalamoun offensive (June–August 2014)]], the village was surrounded by Hezbollah and Syrian Army forces. Tfail is also considered one of the highest villages in Lebanon with an elevation of 1660 meters.{{cn|date=November 2017}}
